radiographic_examinations.findings: The visualized lung bases demonstrate dependent atelectasis without definite consolidation or effusion. The cecum is atypically located in the mid upper abdomen, normal in caliber. The appendix measures up to 9 mm, with marginal mucosal hyperenhancement and possible mild periappendiceal fat stranding. No focal liver lesions, no bowel abnormalities, no free fluid or air.
